ead>Scope and Content Notes</head><p>Series includes legal materials, employment records, photographs, etc.  The scrapbook covers Peter Gregg's acting career.  It includes Carnegie Tech, Off-Broadway, and Broadway programs, photographs, Equity Contracts, clippings, etc.  Also contains several Pittsburgh articles that summarize Gregg's years in New York.  There are two tape recordings of a Pittsburgh Ad Club production, <title render="italic">Ad Cats and Goose Livers</title>, written by Mr. Gregg.  Also includes programs from the Ad Club, Lemonade Opera, and some material relating to Mr. Gregg's radio days.  There are several newsletters and other publications from the Dramatist's Guild, The Lions Club of Pittsburgh, and the Pittsburgh Ad Club.</p></scopecontent><c02 id="aspace_ref6_a3n" level="series"><did><unittitle>Personal history and resumes</unittitle><unitid type="aspace_uri">/repositories/10/archival_objects/188345</unitid><container id="aspace_6a266d1283515663a3f81cf0d577186b" label="Mixed Materials" type="box">6</container><container id="aspace_5aa677a21a95868e32bd2c3854c787e4" parent="aspace_6a266d1283515663a3f81cf0d577186b" type="folder">1</container></did></c02><c02 id="aspace_ref67_39h" level="file"><did><unittitle>Copyrights</unittitle><unitid type="aspace_uri">/repositories/10/archival_objects/188346</unitid><unitdate datechar="creation" normal="1946/1950" type="inclusive">1946-1950</unitdate><container id="aspace_48b55c08648635b815f098a440a16615" label="Mixed Materials" type="box">6</container><container id="aspace_44bf1183b6a6d756a96cd57ba7140879" parent="aspace_48b55c08648635b815f098a440a16615" type="folder">2</container></did></c02><c02 id="aspace_ref68_wvw" level="file"><did><unittitle>Theatrical contracts</unittitle><unitid type="aspace_uri">/repositories/10/archival_objects/188347</unitid><unitdate datechar="creation" normal="1947/1953" type="inclusive">1947-1953</unitdate><container id="aspace_7869bbc470b6ba198ecdc88fb2a63de2" label="Mixed Mat